In conclusion, the most effective way for humans to prevent viral zoonoses is to keep away from ecological niches in natural zoonotic reservoirs.
First, if bats transmit a parental SARS-CoV-2 virus to pangolins, it would be interesting to observe under what circumstances bats and pangolins might share the same ecological niche.
