The drive centres have enabled South Korea to carry out one of the fastest and most comprehensive screening in the world. In Germany, the National Association of Compulsory Health Insurance Physicians said on 2 March that it had the capacity to carry out some 12,000 outpatient tests per day, and that 10,700 patients had been tested in the previous week.
The costs are covered by the sickness insurance if the test is prescribed by a doctor.
